The paper deals with signal processing and sparse transforms, which are typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The use of graph theory and iterative decoding also suggests a possible fit in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also discusses the application of the algorithm to MR images, which suggests a possible fit in the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of sub-linear time complexity suggests a possible fit in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category, although this is less likely given the focus on signal processing.
